---
description: Connect all buttons safely without changing UI
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

For all buttons, pressables, touchables, clickable cards, action icons, menu items, tabs, and interactive UI controls:

Rules:
- ensure every visible interactive element has a valid action
- if a button is intended to navigate, connect it to the correct existing route
- if a button has a missing handler, implement the smallest safe handler
- if a button is intentionally disabled by existing logic, preserve that logic
- do not change button appearance
- do not change button size, placement, label, icon, or styling
- do not replace the component type unless necessary for functionality
- do not add fake placeholder actions that mislead the user

If an interaction target clearly implies a missing route:
- create the missing route using the current project conventions
- keep the screen minimal and visually neutral unless the user asked for full implementation
- preserve existing flow assumptions

If the intended action is unclear:
- prefer the safest behavior
- use existing navigation and naming patterns from the repository
- do not invent unrelated features

Default behavior:
all visible interactive elements should work without changing UI.
